parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of headlights while driving can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights turn off without warning
the low beam headlights shut off while driving
the headlights blink out
the headlights do not reset or come back on
the fog lamps and high beams work fine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system in the driver's door module can cause a fire hazard, leading to vehicle damage and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or fire coming from the driver's door or dashboard
malfunctioning of power windows
door locks
side view mirrors
and heated seats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of headlights while driving can cause a safety hazard, especially at night, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights suddenly going out
inability to switch to regular on position or high beams
instrument panel gauge issues
and speedometer gauge issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to stalling on the highway, which can be a dangerous situation, especially with passengers on board.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not accurately measure the fuel level
the fuel gauge displays the wrong reading
the fuel gauge fails to register gas in the tank
the fuel gauge does not turn off even after refueling
the vehicle stalls due to low fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak or strong gasoline odor can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline present in the vehicle
especially when driving uphill.
